  "prompt": "If I delete someone's conversation (old msgs + new unread message) on WhatsApp without reading it and without opening their chat window, will they receive blue ticks?",
  "response": "No, if you delete someone's conversation on WhatsApp **without opening their chat window** and **without reading the messages**, the sender will **not** receive blue ticks (read receipts). The blue ticks only appear when you open the chat and view the messages.\n\nHere\u2019s what happens when you delete a conversation:\n\n1. **Unread messages**: Since you didn\u2019t open the chat, WhatsApp doesn\u2019t mark the messages as read, and the sender won\u2019t see blue ticks.\n2. **Deleted conversation**: Deleting the conversation removes it from your chat list, but it doesn\u2019t notify the sender or affect their side of the chat.\n\nHowever, if you delete the chat **after reading the messages**, the sender will already have seen the blue ticks, and deleting the chat won\u2019t change that.",
